In article <2v52u1$f5t@agate.berkeley.edu> nobody@shell.portal.com  writes:

> My theory is that OS/2 isn't using the same interrupts to do disk
> access, and the ones that SecureDrive hooks and intercepts.

That is correct.  Anything that works by chaining in to interrupt 013h 
will fail on OS/2 (and NT and Chicago I imagine).  The way around this 
is to use an OS/2 device driver, like Stacker for OS/2 does, but I know 
of no disk encryption package that does this.

